Executive Profile
James R. Helvey IIIFounding Managing Partner, Cassia Capital Partners, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. James R. Helvey, III, also known as Jay, is Founding Managing Partner of Cassia Capital Partners, LLC. Mr. Helvey founded the Cassia Capital Partners in 2011 and serves its Partner. He has been the President of Helvey & Associates, LLC, a financial risk management consulting firm, since its formation in October 2002. Mr. Helvey serves as a Partner and Risk Management Officer and served as a Principal Partner responsible for risk management and portfolio construction ... at CMT Asset Management Limited. He joined the CMT Asset Management Limited in 2004. Mr. Helvey previous work experience includes 15 years at J.P. Morgan, where he was a Managing Director with significant derivative and risk management responsibility. Mr. Helvey served as the Chief Executive Officer of Cygnifi Derivative Services LLC from June 2000 to October 2002. From 1985 to 2000. He worked in several positions at J.P. Morgan & Co., where he served as a Managing Director. Mr. Helvey served as Vice-Chairman of J.P. Morgans Global Risk Management Committee, responsible for monitoring its global risk positions, balance sheet and capital. He serves as Chairman of the Forsyth Country Day School Board of Trustees. Mr. Helvey served as Chairman of Cygnifi Derivative Services LLC from June 2000 to October 2002. He has been a Director of Coca-Cola Bottling Co. Consolidated since January 01, 2016. Mr. Helvey has been an Independent Director at Computer Task Group Inc. since November 10, 2015. He served as Independent Director of Pike Corporation since June 2005 December 2014. Mr. Helvey serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Pike Electric, LLC. He has been Director of Pike Holdings, Inc. since August 1, 2005. Mr. Helvey served as a Board of Trustees of the Wake Forest University, where he serves on the Investment Policy. He serves on the Oakwood Country School Board of Trustees in Morgan Hill. He serves as Director at Piedmont Federal Savings Bank. Mr. Helvey serves as a Director of the Wake Forest Baptist Medical Center. He served as a Director of Cygnifi Derivative Services LLC. Mr. Helvey was also a Fulbright Scholar at the University of Cologne in Germany. He received a Masters of International Affairs in International Finance and Banking from Columbia University and a B.A. in Political Science and German from Wake Forest University.Read Full Background




